    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Genesis",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 48,
        "summary": "Jacob tells of the appearance of God to him in Luz\u2014He adopts Ephraim and Manasseh as his own children\u2014Jacob blesses Joseph\u2014He puts Ephraim before Manasseh\u2014The seed of Ephraim will become a multitude of nations\u2014The children of Israel will come again into the land of their fathers.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass after these things, that one told Joseph, Behold, thy father is sick: and he took with him his two sons, Manasseh and Ephraim.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And one told Jacob, and said, Behold, thy son Joseph cometh unto thee: and Israel strengthened himself, and sat upon the bed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Heb. 11:21.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 47:31.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Jacob said unto Joseph, God Almighty appeared unto me at Luz in the land of Canaan, and blessed me,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 1:14; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:46; 3\u00a0Ne. 4:32; D&C 76:106 (106\u20137); 87:6; Moses 2:1; JS\u2014H 1:29; A\u00a0of\u00a0F 1:11.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 107:54; Abr. 2:6.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 28:19; 35:6; Josh. 18:13.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And said unto me, Behold, I will make thee fruitful, and multiply thee, and I will make of thee a multitude of people; and will give this land to thy seed after thee for an everlasting possession.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Seed of Abraham.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Promised Lands.",
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 142
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 17:8; Abr. 2:6.",
                        "start": 185,
                        "end": 195
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 166,
                        "end": 169
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And now thy two sons, Ephraim and Manasseh, which were born unto thee in the land of Egypt before I came unto thee into Egypt, are mine; as Reuben and Simeon, they shall be mine.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Gen. 48:5\u201311 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Joseph, People of.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 3:13.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 130
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And thy issue, which thou begettest after them, shall be thine, and shall be called after the name of their brethren in their inheritance.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And as for me, when I came from Padan, Rachel died by me in the land of Canaan in the way, when yet there was but a little way to come unto Ephrath: and I buried her there in the way of Ephrath; the same is Beth-lehem.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 35:19.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 109
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 204,
                        "end": 206
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Israel beheld Joseph's sons, and said, Who are these?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Joseph said unto his father, They are my sons, whom God hath given me in this place. And he said, Bring them, I pray thee, unto me, and I will bless them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 49:26.",
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 152
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Now the eyes of Israel were dim for age, so that he could not see. And he brought them near unto him; and he kissed them, and embraced them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 27:1.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 27:27.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Israel said unto Joseph, I had not thought to see thy face: and, lo, God hath shewed me also thy seed.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Joseph brought them out from between his knees, and he bowed himself with his face to the earth.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Joseph took them both, Ephraim in his right hand toward Israel's left hand, and Manasseh in his left hand toward Israel's right hand, and brought them near unto him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 150,
                        "end": 154
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Israel stretched out his right hand, and laid it upon Ephraim's head, who was the younger, and his left hand upon Manasseh's head, guiding his hands wittingly; for Manasseh was the firstborn.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 10:7 (6\u201312); D&C 109:60 (60\u201361); 133:34. TG\u00a0Israel, Joseph, People of.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Septuagint: crossing his hands.",
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 152
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 81
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 177,
                        "end": 180
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And he blessed Joseph, and said, God, before whom my fathers Abraham and Isaac did walk, the God which fed me all my life long unto this day,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Septuagint: them.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 87
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0shepherded; i.e., who was my shepherd.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Angel which redeemed me from all evil, bless the lads; and let my name be named on them, and the name of my fathers Abraham and Isaac; and let them grow into a multitude in the midst of the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 32:29 (24\u201330).",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Joseph, People of; Name.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And when Joseph saw that his father laid his right hand upon the head of Ephraim, it displeased him: and he held up his father's hand, to remove it from Ephraim's head unto Manasseh's head.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hands, Laying on of.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Blessings of.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 80
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0it was wrong in his eyes.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Joseph said unto his father, Not so, my father: for this is the firstborn; put thy right hand upon his head.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And his father refused, and said, I know it, my son, I know it: he also shall become a people, and he also shall be great: but truly his younger brother shall be greater than he, and his seed shall become a multitude of nations.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Josh. 17:14.",
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 121
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Seed of Abraham.",
                        "start": 187,
                        "end": 191
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 1:33.",
                        "start": 207,
                        "end": 216
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 45:24 (24\u201325). TG\u00a0Israel, Joseph, People of.",
                        "start": 220,
                        "end": 227
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And he blessed them that day, saying, In thee shall Israel bless, saying, God make thee as Ephraim and as Manasseh: and he set Ephraim before Manasseh.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0Through thee.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Septuagint: be blessed.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 31:9; D&C 133:34. TG\u00a0Birthright.",
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Israel said unto Joseph, Behold, I die: but God shall be with you, and bring you again unto the land of your fathers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 46:4.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Bondage of, in Egypt.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 80
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Land of; Promised Lands.",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Moreover I have given to thee one portion above thy brethren, which I took out of the hand of the Amorite with my sword and with my bow.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Inheritance.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}